<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_dictionary` row that
    declares the `role_label` String field on the `x_[scope]_case_party`
    custom table inside the scoped application `x_[scope]_case_management`.

    Per AAP Section 0.5.7 (Data-Model Mapping verbatim) for x_[scope]_case_party:

        Field        Type           Constraints
        role_label   String(100)    Mandatory (e.g., Requester, Respondent, Witness)

    Per AAP Section 0.4.3 (Design Pattern Applications):
        "Polymorphic association via single-table choice + UI Policy -
         case_party collapses ArkCase's two association tables
         (acm_person_assoc, acm_person_org_assoc) into one ServiceNow table
         with a Choice discriminator (party_type) and a UI Policy that
         conditionally shows person (reference -> sys_user) or organization
         (reference -> core_company)."

    THIS FIELD CAPTURES THE BUSINESS-DOMAIN ROLE that the linked party plays
    relative to its parent case - e.g., "Requester", "Respondent", "Witness",
    "Subject of Inquiry", "Notified Party", "Counsel", etc. It is the SEMANTIC
    LABEL that operators use to make sense of why a particular Person or
    Organization is associated to a particular case. Without role_label, a
    party row would only carry the polymorphism discriminator (party_type =
    Person | Organization) and the reference (person -> sys_user OR
    organization -> core_company), but NOT the answer to "in what capacity
    is this party associated to this case?". role_label answers that
    question and is therefore mandatory: every party association MUST
    declare its role.

    role_label IS DELIBERATELY A FREE-FORM String, NOT A Choice. Even
    though the user prompt and AAP Section 0.5.7 give three example values
    ("Requester, Respondent, Witness"), the field type is String(100) -
    NOT Choice. This is intentional per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim and
    enables three usage patterns that a Choice field would block:
      1. EXTENSIBILITY: New role labels can be introduced ad-hoc by
         operators without requiring a sys_choice update or an Update
         Set re-deployment. AAP Section 0.5.7 lists three examples but
         does NOT enumerate an exhaustive set; real-world case-management
         vocabularies routinely include additional roles (e.g., "Co-
         Complainant", "Authorized Representative", "Legal Guardian",
         "Beneficiary", "Vendor of Record") that vary by jurisdiction
         and case type. Free-form String accommodates this without
         schema changes.
      2. JURISDICTION-SPECIFIC LOCALIZATION: A scoped POC deployed in
         one country may use "Witness" while another uses "Witness/Bystander"
         or a translated label - free-form String permits this without
         per-jurisdiction sys_choice maintenance.
      3. ARKCASE PARITY: The source-side ArkCase fields that role_label
         collapses are also free-form Strings, not enumerated Choices
         (see source-side reference below). Forcing a Choice list on the
         POC would be a tighter constraint than ArkCase imposed, which
         would require active justification per AAP Section 0.7.1
         ("Preserve the user-prompt's data-model field set verbatim -
         no additions, no renames, no type relaxations"). The verbatim
         AAP type "String(100)" is honored here.

    Operationally, the field surfaces in the following places:
      - On the auto-generated x_[scope]_case_party form (AAP Section 0.4.4
        Internal user UI), as a single-line text input below party_type
        and beside person/organization. The platform renders an asterisk
        because mandatory=true.
      - On the auto-generated x_[scope]_case_party list view, as a column
        showing role at-a-glance (e.g., a list filtered to "all parties
        on case CASE0000007" might show three rows with role_labels
        "Requester", "Respondent", "Witness").
      - On the parent x_[scope]_case form's Related List of parties (per
        AAP Section 0.4.4), where role_label appears beside party_type
        and the resolved person/organization display value so an
        operator reviewing a case sees both WHAT KIND of party each
        association is (Person vs Organization) AND IN WHAT CAPACITY
        (the role_label).
      - In the seed data scripts at
        ../seed-data/parties/x_[scope]_case_party_demo_*.xml and
        ../scripts/seed_demo_data.js (AAP Section 0.7.4 minimum demo-
        data thresholds: "at least one Person and one Organization
        party per demo case to exercise the polymorphic UI policy"),
        every fabricated party row populates role_label with a
        synthetic, non-PII role string (e.g., "Requester",
        "Respondent", "Witness", "Subject", "Notified Party").

    Semantic source-side reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported):
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-person-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/person/model/PersonAssociation.java
        line 93-94:
            @Column(name = "cm_person_assoc_person_type", nullable = false)
            private String personType;
        ArkCase's PersonAssociation entity carried a free-form, mandatory
        String column `personType` whose values were domain-specific
        labels indicating the role of a person relative to a parent
        object. Examples observed in the ArkCase corpus include
        "Initiator", "Originator", "Witness", "Subject", "Custodian".
        See acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin's
        usage of `getPersonAssociations()` filtered by personType to
        derive originator (case requester), reviewer, etc. Note that
        ArkCase's column was nullable=false (i.e., mandatory at the
        JPA level), which the POC honors via `mandatory=true` on this
        ServiceNow dictionary entry.
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-person-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/person/model/PersonOrganizationAssociation.java
        lines 93-97:
            @Column(name = "cm_person_to_org_assoc_type")
            private String personToOrganizationAssociationType;

            @Column(name = "cm_org_to_person_assoc_type")
            private String organizationToPersonAssociationType;
        ArkCase's PersonOrganizationAssociation entity carried TWO
        free-form String columns describing the bidirectional role of
        a person relative to an organization: how the person related
        TO the organization (e.g., "Employee", "Officer", "Member") and
        how the organization related TO the person (e.g., "Employer",
        "Sponsor", "Affiliate"). The bidirectional model was useful for
        the full ArkCase domain but is intentionally simplified for the
        POC: the ServiceNow target collapses both ArkCase association
        tables into one polymorphic table (x_[scope]_case_party) per
        AAP Section 0.4.3, and the bidirectional pair of relationship-
        type columns collapses into ONE role_label column representing
        the role of the party relative to the CASE (not relative to
        another party). This is a deliberate simplification per AAP
        Section 0.1.1 ("proof-of-concept (POC) functional re-platforming,
        not a one-to-one feature port") and AAP Section 0.4.3
        ("polymorphic association via single-table choice + UI Policy").
      - The ServiceNow target therefore COLLAPSES THREE ArkCase concepts
        (PersonAssociation.personType, PersonOrganizationAssociation
        .personToOrganizationAssociationType, PersonOrganizationAssociation
        .organizationToPersonAssociationType) into ONE role_label String
        column. This is consistent with AAP Section 0.4.3's
        "polymorphic association via single-table choice + UI Policy"
        pattern and AAP Section 0.1.2's "Persistence transformation:
        JPA/Hibernate -> Glide records" rule.
      - The field name is `role_label` (lowercase, snake_case, two words
        joined by underscore; NOT `roleLabel`, NOT `role`, NOT
        `personType`, NOT `association_type`, NOT `relationship_role`)
        per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim. Snake_case aligns with
        ServiceNow's platform-native column-naming convention and
        matches the snake_case used by every other field on this
        scoped table (case, party_type, person, organization).
      - The label "Role Label" (Title Case, two words separated by space)
        per the agent prompt's Phase 2 verbatim. The two-word label
        matches the two-word internal name and reads naturally as a
        form field label and list column header.

    Constraints honored (AAP Sections 0.5.7, 0.7.1, 0.7.2, 0.7.4):
      - Scope-namespace exclusivity: `<name>` resolves to
        `x_[scope]_case_party` within the scoped application, and
        `<sys_scope>` / `<sys_package>` bind THIS dictionary record to
        the same scope by `source` attribute lookup. NO global-scope
        writes - the OOB tables `task`, `incident`, `sys_user`,
        `core_company`, etc. are never modified by this dictionary
        entry or any other artifact in the Update Set. The `[scope]`
        placeholder is preserved per AAP convention; the PDI auto-
        assigns the actual scope id at App Engine Studio creation time.
      - Zero hardcoded cross-reference sys_ids: the `<sys_scope>` and
        `<sys_package>` text-node values resolve by scope source name
        (`x_[scope]_case_management`), not by literal sys_id. The
        `<sys_id>` text-node value is THIS record's own deterministic
        primary key (MD5 of the canonical field identifier
        `x_[scope]_case_party.role_label`) and is NOT a reference to
        any other record. The MD5 derivation guarantees that re-
        generation of this Update Set on any agent run produces a
        byte-identical `<sys_id>` (no random UUIDs), which is required
        for clean Update-Set re-import on a fresh PDI without creating
        duplicate sys_dictionary rows. The same derivation pattern is
        used by every sys_dictionary record in this Update Set (e.g.,
        x_[scope]_case_party.party_type     -> 5e02afdbd2f05f407e986015e93d1238,
        x_[scope]_case.requester_name       -> 696e73e041d826fe2d43a3f259acd1f1).
        Verified:
            python3 -c "import hashlib; print(hashlib.md5(b'x_[scope]_case_party.role_label').hexdigest())"
        prints 04c189886307f35757d6fc5f94b9074f (matches sys_id below).
      - mandatory=true at the dictionary level. AAP Section 0.5.7
        verbatim marks role_label as Mandatory ("Mandatory (e.g.,
        Requester, Respondent, Witness)"). A party row without a
        role_label is semantically incomplete: it identifies WHO is
        associated to a case (via the person or organization reference)
        but not WHY - leaving the row uninterpretable to anyone who
        reads it later. The mandatory flag enforces this at the
        dictionary level so the platform's mandatory-flag enforcement
        runs at every entry point: the auto-generated form (where the
        user sees a red asterisk and cannot save without a value), the
        Table API (which rejects POST/PATCH bodies that omit
        role_label), the GlideRecord.insert() path used by
        ../scripts/seed_demo_data.js (which throws if the field is
        unset), and any future scripted REST endpoints that touch
        case_party. ArkCase's source-side equivalent
        PersonAssociation.personType also carried nullable=false at
        the JPA level, so this constraint preserves source-side intent
        per AAP Section 0.7.1.
      - read_only=false: case_manager and case_agent (the latter only
        within their "Assigned only" cases per AAP Section 0.5.6)
        MAY edit role_label after initial creation - for example, to
        correct a row erroneously created with role_label="Witness"
        when the actual capacity was "Subject", or to evolve the
        labeling convention as a case progresses (e.g., a person
        initially labeled "Witness" who later becomes a "Co-Respondent"
        once additional facts emerge). The read_only=false setting
        permits the write through the standard form, the Table API,
        and the seed scripts. Field-level write authorization is
        governed by the table-level ACLs in
        ../acl/x_[scope]_case_party_*.xml; AAP Section 0.5.6 does NOT
        list role_label among the field-level-ACL-required fields
        (only case.assigned_group and case.assigned_agent carry
        field-level ACLs).
      - default_value is EMPTY (no implicit default). AAP Section 0.5.7
        does NOT specify a default for role_label, and forcing the
        user to choose makes the role-assignment intent EXPLICIT. A
        silent default (e.g., "Requester") would silently commit
        rows whose actual role differs, polluting Related List
        renderings and making it impossible to distinguish "the
        operator chose Requester" from "the operator forgot to fill
        in role_label and the system defaulted". The agent prompt's
        Phase 4 explicitly mandates `<default_value/>` empty.
      - audit=false per AAP Section 0.3.1 minimal-change clause and
        the agent prompt's Phase 4. Role-label changes are descriptive
        metadata corrections, not regulated lifecycle events. The
        standard sys_* audit columns at the table level
        (sys_created_on, sys_created_by, sys_updated_on,
        sys_updated_by) capture record-level changes; per-field audit
        on role_label is unnecessary overhead for a POC.
      - max_length=100 EXACTLY per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim. NOT
        4000 (description, the long-form free-text body), NOT 255
        (subject, the case summary line), NOT 40 (party_type, status,
        priority - the controlled-vocabulary identifier-style strings).
        100 chars comfortably accommodates the example labels
        ("Requester" 9 chars, "Respondent" 10 chars, "Witness" 7
        chars) plus longer real-world variants ("Authorized Legal
        Representative" 32 chars, "Co-Complainant Designee" 23 chars,
        "Subject of Inquiry / Investigation" 35 chars), and matches
        the sibling x_[scope]_case.requester_name column's 100-char
        ceiling for symmetric storage of identity-and-role strings.
      - internal_type=string is correct for free-form text fields up
        to 4000 chars in ServiceNow. The platform's form engine
        renders a String column with max_length<=255 as a single-line
        text input (no `attributes` override required for this
        presentation), which matches the single-line label expected
        on the party form and Related List.
      - choice=0 = "Free-form String, no choice list" (NOT 3 like the
        sibling party_type field at ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_party_type.xml,
        and NOT 1 like a choice-with-suggestions field). This is the
        explicit configuration that distinguishes role_label as a
        free-form text field. Despite the example values ("Requester",
        "Respondent", "Witness") appearing in AAP Section 0.5.7, the
        field is INTENTIONALLY free-form per the AAP's verbatim type
        annotation "String(100)" - not "Choice". Free-form supports
        the extensibility, localization, and ArkCase-parity arguments
        described above.
      - unique=false: multiple parties on multiple cases (or even on
        the same case) may legitimately share the same role_label
        (e.g., a case with two witnesses both labeled "Witness", or
        a class action with many "Co-Complainant" parties).
        Uniqueness at the row level is delegated to the auto-
        generated `sys_id` of each x_[scope]_case_party row.
      - text_index=false per the agent prompt's Phase 6 verbatim.
        Unlike subject (text_index=true, the primary search target
        across the case list) and description (text_index=true, the
        long-form searchable body), role_label is a short categorical
        label that does not need to participate in the case-list
        quick-search index for the POC. Internal users wanting to
        filter by role_label can still do so via the standard list-
        view condition builder (which works without a text index for
        short String columns at POC data volumes).
      - spell_check=false per the agent prompt's Phase 6 verbatim.
        Role labels are domain-specific terminology (often capitalized
        proper nouns and compound terms like "Co-Complainant") that
        are not amenable to dictionary-based spell-checking - any
        spell-check suggestions on a role-label field would generate
        false-positive squiggles that degrade UX without adding value.
      - attributes is EMPTY per the agent prompt's Phase 6 verbatim.
        Edge Encryption support is intentionally out of POC scope.
      - No reference target: this is a free-form String field, not a
        Reference field. All `<reference*>` elements are empty and
        `<table_reference>false</table_reference>`. The POC
        deliberately does NOT model role_label as a Reference to a
        catalog table because:
          (i) AAP Section 0.5.7's literal type for role_label is
              "String(100)" - NOT a reference. The exact field type
              and constraint matrix is preserved verbatim per AAP
              Section 0.7.1 ("Preserve the user-prompt's data-model
              field set verbatim - no additions, no renames, no type
              relaxations").
          (ii) A Reference target would require introducing a NEW
              parent table (e.g., x_[scope]_case_party_role_catalog)
              that holds the canonical role labels - which AAP
              Section 0.3.2 (Minimal-Change Clause: "MUST NOT add
              modules, workflows, portal pages, tables, or
              integrations beyond the defined scope") explicitly
              prohibits. The POC has exactly THREE custom tables:
              x_[scope]_case, x_[scope]_case_task, x_[scope]_case_party.
              No fourth table for role catalogs is permitted.
      - No PII: per AAP Section 0.7.2 (No-PII constraint, "Synthetic
        data only"). NO real role labels tied to identifiable
        individuals are placed in this column at any point in the
        build. Demo seed values are domain-generic role strings such
        as "Requester", "Respondent", "Witness", "Subject", "Notified
        Party" - none of which are tied to real individuals or real
        cases.

    Cross-references (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      - This record MUST load AFTER:
          * ../tables/x_[scope]_case_party.xml (parent table, since
            `<name>x_[scope]_case_party</name>` references the table
            by name and the platform refuses to materialize a
            sys_dictionary row whose `name` refers to a non-existent
            table).
          * ../app/sys_app/x_[scope]_case_management.xml and
            ../app/sys_scope/x_[scope].xml (the scoped-application
            and scope records, since `<sys_scope>` and `<sys_package>`
            resolve via `source` attribute lookup against the scope
            source name `x_[scope]_case_management` - both records
            must exist before this dictionary entry can resolve them).

      - This record MUST load BEFORE:
          * ../seed-data/parties/x_[scope]_case_party_demo_*.xml
            (every fabricated demo party row populates role_label
            via setValue('role_label', '...'), which requires the
            column to exist in the dictionary).
          * ../scripts/seed_demo_data.js (the idempotent server-
            side seed script writes role_label on every demo party
            row; the column must exist in the dictionary before the
            script can run successfully).
          * ../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml
            (does not directly reference role_label, but is part of
            the same form layout; the platform's form-rendering
            engine inspects all dictionary entries on the table when
            rendering the form, so role_label must be registered
            before the UI Policy is activated).

    Validation Gate (AAP Section 0.7.3, Gate 1):
        "Data model: All 3 custom tables created with correct fields
         and types - Zero missing mandatory fields"
      This field is one of FIVE mandatory dictionary entries on the
      x_[scope]_case_party table (the others being case, party_type,
      person, organization - though person and organization are
      conditionally mandatory via the UI Policy). It MUST be present
      with mandatory=true, internal_type=string, max_length=100
      EXACTLY per AAP Section 0.5.7. Any deviation will fail Gate 1
      of the validation framework and prevent the Update Set from
      being exported.

    Round-trip integrity (AAP Section 0.7.1):
      - The `<sys_id>` is deterministic (MD5-derived), so re-generation
        of this Update Set always produces the same primary key. This
        means re-importing the Update Set on a fresh PDI updates the
        existing sys_dictionary row in place rather than creating a
        duplicate, which is the only way to satisfy AAP Section 0.7.3
        Gate 7 ("Update Set: Scoped app exported - Update Set loads
        without errors on a fresh PDI instance").
      - All XML element values use straight ASCII quotes; no smart
        quotes that would break XML parsing on import.
      - All boolean fields use lowercase `true` / `false` per
        ServiceNow XML serialization convention.
      - The `<active>true</active>` flag is REQUIRED for the field
        to be visible/usable on the form per the agent prompt's
        Phase 4. An inactive dictionary entry would not appear on
        the form despite mandatory=true, leading to a
        contradictory/broken state.
-->
<record_update table="sys_dictionary">
    <sys_dictionary action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <array>false</array>
        <attributes/>
        <audit>false</audit>
        <calculation/>
        <choice>0</choice>
        <choice_field/>
        <choice_table/>
        <column_label>Role Label</column_label>
        <comments>Mandatory string field capturing the role this party plays for the linked case (e.g., Requester, Respondent, Witness). Replaces ArkCase's PersonAssociation.personType.</comments>
        <create_roles/>
        <default_value/>
        <defaultsort/>
        <delete_roles/>
        <dependent/>
        <dependent_on_field/>
        <display>true</display>
        <dynamic_creation>false</dynamic_creation>
        <dynamic_creation_script/>
        <dynamic_default_value/>
        <dynamic_ref_qual/>
        <element>role_label</element>
        <element_reference>false</element_reference>
        <foreign_database/>
        <function_definition/>
        <function_field>false</function_field>
        <internal_type>string</internal_type>
        <mandatory>true</mandatory>
        <max_length>100</max_length>
        <name>x_[scope]_case_party</name>
        <next_element/>
